	<text>
		<body>
			<div type="entry">
				<pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary71.jpg"/>
				<dateline><date when="1862-05-29">Thursday 29</date>.</dateline>
				<p><name type="weather">A bright pleasant day</name>. We got a <objectName
						type="readable">mail</objectName>, small one, &amp; <objectName
						type="readable">papers</objectName> to the 25th. We heard through <orgName
						type="confederates">rebel</orgName> sources that <persName role="Military"
						type="Banks">Banks</persName> was defeated &amp; 4000 prisoners taken. We
					see by the <objectName type="readable">paper</objectName> that <persName
						role="Military" type="Col.Kenly ">Col. Kenly</persName> with the <orgName
						type="Confederate">1st Maryland</orgName> was defeated, &amp; I judged that
						<persName role="Military" type="Banks">Banks</persName> was in a precarious
					condition. The <orgName type="Union">Reg’t</orgName> moved by companies, and 6
					companies were moved, so that we stay here tonight yet. <persName
						role="Military" key="Daniel Bible"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper022"
						cert="high" type="real">Adjt. Bible</persName> returned this evening. </p>
				<pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary72.jpg"/>
				<fw><date when="1862-05-29">Thursday 29</date>.</fw>
				<p><persName type="Bible">He</persName> looks well. <persName type="Bible"
						>He</persName> gives <orgName type="regiment">us</orgName> glowing
						<objectName type="readable">acts</objectName> of the <orgName
						type="Military">refutation of the 51st</orgName> - <persName type="Bible"
						>He</persName> tells a good story on <persName>old Brower of
							<placeName>Norristown</placeName></persName> who speaking of the
						<objectName type="equipment">sword</objectName>
					<persName role="Military" type="Jones">Jones</persName> sent home, “Just to
					think I never thought there was much in him and he had to kill the men to take
					it.” &amp; some other one remarked that in after years he would regret having
					killed a fellow creature.” Rec’d a <objectName type="readable"
						>letter</objectName> from <persName role="Military" type="John"
						>John</persName> with the news that <persName role="Military"
						type="Personnel">May Husburgh</persName> had eloped with <persName
						role="Military" type="Lineweaver">Lineweaver</persName>. It is hard because
					some of the members of <orgName type="Church">M H’s church at <placeName
							type="Lebanon" cert="high" key="Pennsylvania"
							ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl067"
								>Lebanon</placeName></orgName> are involved in it, and it will never be pleasant
					to remain there - It is an outrage because she is only 17 and he 35 years old.
					Stolen to from our <placeName>house</placeName>. <persName role="Military"
						type="John">John</persName> is particularly indignant on that account. The
					minister who married them, they are determined to prosecute, &amp; wish for
					conspiracy. <persName role="Military" type="real" cert="high" key="Thomas Grier"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper076"
						>Tom Grier</persName> said that <persName role="Military"
						key="Edward Stanly"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper027"
						>Gov. Stanly</persName> has commenced his reign by suppressing <orgName
						type="School">Colyers night schools</orgName>, and the [d---] are in terror
					because It is reported that he said they would all be remanded to their masters.
					One said he would put a <objectName type="equipment">knife</objectName> in his
						<objectName type="body">gut</objectName> before he would go back to his
					Massa. This is all right. It takes all <persName type="Abe">old Abes</persName>
					Wisdom to counteract the rascally radicalism of such men as <persName
						role="General" type="Phelps">Phelps</persName> and <persName role="General"
						type="Hunter">Hunter</persName>, who are, by the way, among the best
					Generals in the service. The <orgName type="Military">17 Mass</orgName> returned
					from picket duty. I understand that the whole of the<orgName type="Military">
						1st Division</orgName> are to be encamped here.</p>
			</div>
